        "summary": "The National Skill Training Institute for Women in Noida, has invited applications for admission to its National Council for Vocational Education and Training for the academic session 2026-27. The Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship informed that interested candidates can check the detailed eligibility criteria, available trades, and other admission guidelines, and submit their appl",
        "article": "The National Skill Training Institute for Women in Noida, has invited applications for admission to its National Council for Vocational Education and Training for the academic session 2026-27. The Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship informed that interested candidates can check the detailed eligibility criteria, available trades, and other admission guidelines, and submit their applications online through the institute&#8217;s admission portal at nstiwnoida.dgtmsde.in . The institute offers industry-oriented training in a wide range of conventional and emerging sectors, including Artificial Intelligence, Drone Technology, Semiconductor Technology, 5G Networks, Fashion Design, Computer Applications and Cosmetology among others. The last date for submission of online applications is the 12th of this month. The Ministry added that these programmes are aligned with the National Skills Qualifications Framework, enabling trainees to pursue higher education and access various employment opportunities.",
